 november 20 2010 excerpt on november 12 during my most recent visit to the yongbyon nuclear complex with stanford university colleagues john w lewis and robert carlin we were shown a 25 to 30 megawatt electric mwe experimental light water reactor lwr in the early stages of construction it is north korea's first attempt at lwr technology and we were told it is proceeding with strictly indigenous resources and talent the target date for operation was said to be 2012 which appears much too optimistic download pdf+ complete modified november 2010 pdf heckeryongbyon pdf 140.4 kb parent events north korea's yongbyon nuclear complex a presentation by siegfried s hecker at the korea economic institute november 23 2010 special event siegfried s hecker robert carlin pdf+ presentation available parent research nuclear security and risk topics nuclear power nuclear safety and security nuclear security & risk north korea search cisac publications everything publication news cisac team discovers new north korean uranium enrichment facility november 19 2010 cisac fsi stanford in the news publications of interest denuclearizing north korea siegfried s hecker bulletin of the atomic scientists vol vo 64 no 2 2008 pdf+ cover report on north korean nuclear program siegfried s hecker cisac 2006 pdf+ cover report of visit to north korea to senate foreign relations committee siegfried s hecker 2008 pdf+ cover what i found in yongbyon and why it matters siegfried s hecker american physical society vol 20 3 2011 html+ cover support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
